WEBVTT

00:11.959 --> 00:13.709
[Ray]
Previously on  Ray Donovan...

00:13.709 --> 00:14.750
[Bridget]
You never told me

00:14.750 --> 00:16.375
how Bridget died.

00:16.375 --> 00:17.625
[Ray]
She was high on drugs.

00:17.625 --> 00:18.792
She jumped off a roof.

00:18.792 --> 00:20.291
[Finney]
So I had a contract drawn up

00:20.291 --> 00:23.125
to buy you and your company
lock, stock, and barrel.

00:23.125 --> 00:24.500
I'm not for sale.

00:24.500 --> 00:26.125
So we're still negotiating.

00:26.125 --> 00:27.417
Special Agent Barnes.

00:27.417 --> 00:29.083
Who killed Sully Sullivan?

00:29.083 --> 00:30.333
Mickey Donovan.

00:30.333 --> 00:32.333
Any pimp messes with you
on the street,

00:32.333 --> 00:33.959
- I'm there in a shot.
- Who's working on the street?

00:33.959 --> 00:36.083
These girls don't
walk the streets.

00:36.083 --> 00:38.125
This isn't 1979.

00:38.125 --> 00:39.458
You put skin shots
on the Internet,

00:39.458 --> 00:40.333
and that's how the johns
find you.

00:40.333 --> 00:41.792
Mm-hmm.

00:41.792 --> 00:43.000
[Mickey]
We supply the girls cocaine

00:43.000 --> 00:44.959
and the ability to front cash.

00:44.959 --> 00:46.750
They sell the johns coke,
and when Johnny wants to do 'em

00:46.750 --> 00:49.333
a second time, can't pay for it,
we loan 'em the money.

00:49.333 --> 00:50.625
We split the proceeds
with the girls,

00:50.625 --> 00:54.000
get them upselling
these fuckers, expand.

00:54.000 --> 00:55.125
[Abby]
Got a thing

00:55.125 --> 00:56.583
for the muscle girl, Bunch?

00:56.583 --> 00:57.959
Those Mexicans
won't pay their dues.

00:57.959 --> 00:59.125
So you really gonna
kick us out?

00:59.125 --> 01:00.667
That's the rules.

01:00.667 --> 01:01.834
You like rules?

01:03.083 --> 01:04.792
I want you to come
for dinner tonight.

01:04.792 --> 01:05.625
It's important to me.

01:05.625 --> 01:06.583
What's going on?

01:06.583 --> 01:08.542
She wants you home.

01:08.542 --> 01:11.417
Troy's most recent distraction
is the wife of a Navy SEAL.

01:11.417 --> 01:13.000
I need you to
handle this quickly.

01:13.000 --> 01:14.834
I'm authorizing you
to go up to $500,000.

01:14.834 --> 01:18.333
I'm not taking the money.

01:18.333 --> 01:19.625
You're the third guy
they sent.

01:19.625 --> 01:20.834
You ready, ding?

01:20.834 --> 01:21.875
I'm here, ain't I?

01:21.875 --> 01:23.500
[crowd yelling]

01:26.000 --> 01:27.709
Who's the ding,
motherfucker?

01:27.709 --> 01:29.375
Who's the ding, motherfucker?

01:32.458 --> 01:33.417
[door clanks shut]

01:35.041 --> 01:37.542
Sorry, sweetheart.
I'm not gonna make it.

01:37.542 --> 01:38.917
Take the money.

01:55.208 --> 01:58.333
Sufjan Stevens'
"Seven Swans" playing

01:58.333 --> 02:03.208
♪♪♪

02:19.542 --> 02:22.709
Daddy?

02:22.709 --> 02:23.917
Oh, my God.
What happened?

02:27.792 --> 02:30.500
[sighs]

02:30.500 --> 02:33.542
I'm sorry I didn't
make it home for dinner.

02:33.542 --> 02:36.208
Oh.

02:36.208 --> 02:38.792
Mom gave your food
to the dog.

02:38.792 --> 02:42.458
[chuckles]
Yeah?

02:42.458 --> 02:46.458
She thinks you're still
punishing her over that cop.

02:46.458 --> 02:48.500
I'm not.

02:50.542 --> 02:52.625
Why didn't you come?

03:00.583 --> 03:01.959
Daddy?

03:15.709 --> 03:20.375
♪ We didn't sleep too late ♪

03:20.375 --> 03:23.291
Go back to sleep,
sweetheart.

03:23.291 --> 03:27.709
♪ There was a fire
In the yard ♪

03:27.709 --> 03:31.125
[barking]

03:31.125 --> 03:35.500
♪ All of the trees
Were in light ♪

03:35.500 --> 03:39.417
[barking]

03:39.417 --> 03:43.166
- [vehicle departing]
- ♪ They had no faces to show ♪

03:43.166 --> 03:45.750
♪♪♪

03:45.750 --> 03:48.667
♪ I saw a sign ♪

03:48.667 --> 03:51.709
♪ In the sky ♪

03:51.709 --> 03:53.166
[gasps]

03:53.166 --> 03:56.834
♪ Seven swans,
Seven swans ♪

03:56.834 --> 03:59.625
♪ Seven swans ♪

03:59.625 --> 04:01.041
[groans]

04:01.041 --> 04:05.375
♪ I heard a voice
In my mind ♪

04:05.375 --> 04:08.333
♪♪♪

04:08.333 --> 04:12.542
♪ I will try, I will try,
I will try... ♪

04:12.542 --> 04:15.041
Yeah. Sure. Yeah, if I ever
need more wrestling lessons,

04:15.041 --> 04:16.458
I'll be glad to go out.

04:16.458 --> 04:19.875
Yeah. Okay, bye.

04:19.875 --> 04:23.750
Ugh, don't you just hate it
when men try to manhandle you?

04:23.750 --> 04:27.333
[Helen]
I don't remember.

04:27.333 --> 04:29.875
Oh, you fixed it!
What was wrong?

04:29.875 --> 04:31.792
[Stanley]
It was a short.

04:31.792 --> 04:33.917
You know, you people
are so careless.

04:33.917 --> 04:35.625
You should never bend
an electrical cord.

04:35.625 --> 04:37.375
- Otherwise--
- [electricity buzzing]

04:37.375 --> 04:39.417
[women shriek,
audience laughs]

04:39.417 --> 04:40.834
- What happened?
- Mr. Roper.

04:40.834 --> 04:41.875
[Helen]
Stanley was showing us

04:41.875 --> 04:43.041
how not to get a shock.

04:43.041 --> 04:45.333
[audience laughs]

04:45.333 --> 04:46.500
[Stanley]
Will you put some clothes on?

04:46.500 --> 04:47.709
My wife's here.

04:47.709 --> 04:49.208
Mind your
own business, Stanley.

04:49.208 --> 04:50.959
[audience laughs]

04:50.959 --> 04:52.667
What if the towel slips?

04:52.667 --> 04:55.458
Mind your own business,
Stanley.

04:55.458 --> 04:57.333
Jack, you have some
shaving cream on your face.

04:57.333 --> 04:58.333
Oh, thank you.

04:58.333 --> 05:00.375
No, Jack!

05:00.375 --> 05:02.750
Mind your own business,
Chrissy.

05:05.917 --> 05:08.792
[indistinct chatter on TV]

05:15.250 --> 05:18.125
[man on TV]
Bob?

05:18.125 --> 05:20.000
Here they come.

05:22.291 --> 05:24.083
Let's put a few shots
over their heads.

05:24.083 --> 05:26.083
That should scatter them.

05:26.083 --> 05:29.166
[gunfire on TV]

05:35.125 --> 05:36.333
What the fuck
happened to you?

05:40.750 --> 05:41.792
Lost a fight.

05:43.542 --> 05:45.458
Finney offered us a job?

05:47.125 --> 05:48.417
Why didn't you take it?

05:48.417 --> 05:52.750
I spent 25 years
being told what to do.

05:52.750 --> 05:53.834
I'm done.

05:58.458 --> 06:02.667
Spare key is
in the third drawer of my desk.

06:02.667 --> 06:05.250
And your coffeemaker's busted,

06:05.250 --> 06:07.458
so I got you a new one.

06:11.917 --> 06:14.834
[gunfire and screaming on TV]

06:18.917 --> 06:20.333
[Michelle]
What is this shit?

06:20.333 --> 06:23.500
Doughnuts and coke.
Breakfast of champions.

06:23.500 --> 06:25.333
I got some new thoughts
about how we might work together

06:25.333 --> 06:26.625
to improve your business.

06:26.625 --> 06:28.208
- No.
- Not happening.

06:28.208 --> 06:29.333
- No.
- No.

06:29.333 --> 06:31.458
Wait.
Give Mick a chance.

06:31.458 --> 06:33.208
- We did yesterday.
- Why?

06:33.208 --> 06:35.083
[Mick] I get why you ladies
might be hesitant.

06:35.083 --> 06:37.500
My ideas yesterday
must have struck you

06:37.500 --> 06:38.709
as a little bit old-school.

06:38.709 --> 06:40.500
- You think?
- Uh, a little bit.

06:40.500 --> 06:43.500
If you don't want to listen,
hey, you're free to go.

06:43.500 --> 06:44.959
But if you stay,

06:44.959 --> 06:46.625
I'm gonna let you in
on a vision I have

06:46.625 --> 06:48.917
of a way we can all
get rich together.

06:50.458 --> 06:53.291
Look, this cocaine?
See this cocaine?

06:53.291 --> 06:55.667
This is for you to sell.

06:55.667 --> 06:59.875
Each one of you can take as much
as you think you can move.

06:59.875 --> 07:02.959
We split the profits.

07:02.959 --> 07:06.417
This is my son.
You know Daryll.

07:06.417 --> 07:09.041
He has a livery license
and is a professional boxer.

07:09.041 --> 07:10.875
He'll be your personal driver
and bodyguard.

07:10.875 --> 07:12.834
As for me, I'll take care
of your advertising

07:12.834 --> 07:14.000
and your time management.

07:14.000 --> 07:15.250
I'll place your ads,

07:15.250 --> 07:17.959
handle your incoming
phone calls,

07:17.959 --> 07:20.834
keep track
of your whereabouts from here.

07:20.834 --> 07:23.417
Let us take care of you
for one day.

07:23.417 --> 07:25.500
One day.

07:25.500 --> 07:27.333
End of the day,

07:27.333 --> 07:30.750
you'd rather be
independent operators,

07:30.750 --> 07:32.834
no harm, no foul.

07:32.834 --> 07:34.834
Mm.

07:34.834 --> 07:35.917
One day.

07:39.291 --> 07:40.917
[man on TV]
Dishonesty,

07:40.917 --> 07:42.583
fraud,

07:42.583 --> 07:44.375
corruption.

07:44.375 --> 07:48.583
Governor Tom Verona
is in bed with big business.

07:48.583 --> 07:50.417
He purports to be
for the little man,

07:50.417 --> 07:53.125
but who does
he really serve?

07:53.125 --> 07:55.875
On November 3rd,
vote against our tax money

07:55.875 --> 07:58.208
making the rich richer.

07:58.208 --> 07:59.709
A vote no on Verona...

07:59.709 --> 08:02.500
Hey. You got a minute?

08:02.500 --> 08:05.333
- Hey, Bunch.
- This ad is paid for...

08:05.333 --> 08:07.917
I need $20,000
from my settlement fund.

08:07.917 --> 08:09.750
[sighs]

08:13.208 --> 08:14.917
What's going on?

08:16.250 --> 08:18.750
I'm investing
in a business.

08:20.709 --> 08:22.542
Mexican wrestling?

08:23.542 --> 08:25.500
Luchadores.

08:25.500 --> 08:27.834
They're training at the gym.

08:27.834 --> 08:31.959
Thought we could put on
a few shows.

08:31.959 --> 08:32.917
Seriously?

08:32.917 --> 08:35.375
[cell phone ringing]

08:37.792 --> 08:39.291
Yeah.

08:39.291 --> 08:41.125
Terry got in a fight
with an Aryan.

08:41.125 --> 08:42.959
- Is he all right?
- He's fine.

08:42.959 --> 08:44.291
The fucking Aryan
is dead.

08:44.291 --> 08:45.625
Where is he?

08:45.625 --> 08:47.458
Isolation, for now.

08:47.458 --> 08:48.959
Warden's talking
about moving him.

08:48.959 --> 08:51.125
- Keep him there.
- I don't know how long I can.

08:51.125 --> 08:52.625
I'm coming out.

08:54.583 --> 08:56.291
[Bunchy]
I'm serious, Ray.

08:56.291 --> 08:59.125
We can make a lot of money
for the Fite Club.

08:59.125 --> 09:00.291
It's a front, Bunch.

09:00.291 --> 09:03.083
It's not supposed to
make money.

09:18.166 --> 09:20.250
So Mr. Finney is concerned
about the story

09:20.250 --> 09:22.000
the remaining kidnapper
may tell the police.

09:22.000 --> 09:23.667
Not my problem.

09:23.667 --> 09:25.458
I understand,
but he'd still like

09:25.458 --> 09:27.208
both sides
of the story insured.

09:27.208 --> 09:29.083
I already signed
his nondisclosure.

09:29.083 --> 09:32.583
Mr. Finney would prefer
if you reconsider his offer.

09:32.583 --> 09:34.792
Having you in his employ
would make him sleep easier.

09:34.792 --> 09:36.250
Who the fuck
are you?

09:36.250 --> 09:37.458
Mr. Goldberg's
our family attorney.

09:37.458 --> 09:39.875
Mr. Donovan, you'll find it
better to keep

09:39.875 --> 09:41.166
Mr. Finney as a friend.

09:42.041 --> 09:43.542
Is that a threat?

09:43.542 --> 09:45.917
Just telling you
which way the wind blows.

09:47.709 --> 09:50.291
I already told him.
I'm not for sale.

09:52.166 --> 09:55.000
[pop music plays on computer]

09:55.000 --> 09:57.875
♪♪♪

09:57.875 --> 09:59.875
[door opens]

09:59.875 --> 10:03.709
No one's banned so far.
Things are looking up.

10:03.709 --> 10:05.041
[scoffs]

10:05.041 --> 10:06.166
Oh, shit.

10:06.166 --> 10:07.667
Looking up, Pop?

10:07.667 --> 10:08.959
I mean, we spent all that money
that you got

10:08.959 --> 10:10.500
from the Armenians
on that coke

10:10.500 --> 10:12.500
just so six hookers
can get high all day.

10:12.500 --> 10:15.041
They understand the value
of a solid business plan.

10:15.041 --> 10:17.709
- They're smart enough.
- Hell, no.

10:17.709 --> 10:20.125
All they understand is
coke makes them feel great.

10:20.125 --> 10:21.291
Well, they got that right.

10:21.291 --> 10:23.125
What are you
so worried about?

10:23.125 --> 10:25.333
Pop, I'm worried because
those Armenians are gonna

10:25.333 --> 10:27.583
take my fucking Cadillac.
I can feel it.

10:27.583 --> 10:30.333
Just drive the girls.
Have some faith.

10:30.333 --> 10:32.917
You do know
I only have one car, okay?

10:32.917 --> 10:35.583
I mean, how am I supposed to
drive seven girls around?

10:35.583 --> 10:37.750
Oh, what a delightful dilemma.

10:37.750 --> 10:39.125
Get off of me, Pop.
Get off. Get off.

10:39.125 --> 10:40.583
[knock at door]

10:40.583 --> 10:42.500
- [door opens]
- Yeah?

10:42.500 --> 10:43.875
Mick, one of my regulars
is on the way.

10:43.875 --> 10:45.291
Can Audrey stay with you?

10:45.291 --> 10:48.250
Of course. Come on in.
Join the party.

10:48.250 --> 10:51.625
Be good, baby.
Thanks, Mick.

10:55.125 --> 10:58.125
Why the long face?

10:58.125 --> 10:59.709
That's what they say
to the horse, you see,

10:59.709 --> 11:01.750
'cause a horse
has a long face.

11:02.875 --> 11:04.083
[phone rings]

11:04.083 --> 11:07.917
Okay.

11:07.917 --> 11:10.208
Mm.

11:10.208 --> 11:12.083
You got Mickey Donovan.

11:12.083 --> 11:13.959
[woman on phone] You have
a phone call from an inmate

11:13.959 --> 11:16.959
at the California State
Correctional Institution.

11:16.959 --> 11:18.792
Will you accept
the charge?

11:18.792 --> 11:19.750
[beep]

11:19.750 --> 11:21.625
Sure, sure.

11:23.125 --> 11:25.375
[sighs]

11:34.458 --> 11:36.667
What do you got
going on today, Conor?

11:36.667 --> 11:40.291
School.
I don't know.

11:40.291 --> 11:44.166
[sighs]
Dad came home last night.

11:44.166 --> 11:46.542
Really?

11:48.417 --> 11:50.000
He'd been in a fight.
It was weird.

11:50.000 --> 11:53.333
He sat down on my bed,
apologized, and then left.

11:53.333 --> 11:54.625
Oh.

11:54.625 --> 11:57.750
Are you worried
about him?

11:57.750 --> 12:01.500
No, sweetheart.
He's figuring some things out.

12:01.500 --> 12:02.625
Right.

12:02.625 --> 12:04.834
Okay.

12:04.834 --> 12:06.500
You need to sign this.

12:08.250 --> 12:09.667
You got a D?

12:09.667 --> 12:11.583
My teacher says that
I need a tutor.

12:11.583 --> 12:13.166
He said that
public high school

12:13.166 --> 12:15.500
didn't prepare me
for Rossmore's standards.

12:16.834 --> 12:19.875
Jeez, Bridge.

12:19.875 --> 12:20.959
You're getting a D.

12:20.959 --> 12:22.792
Yeah.

12:22.792 --> 12:24.500
Why didn't you
say something before?

12:24.500 --> 12:25.917
It's not some tragedy.

12:25.917 --> 12:27.542
And calculus is hard.

12:27.542 --> 12:28.917
Conor does shitty
all the time.

12:28.917 --> 12:31.083
I know, Bridge, but we went
to a lot of bother

12:31.083 --> 12:32.208
to get you in there.

12:32.208 --> 12:33.792
Bother?

12:33.792 --> 12:36.875
You just put me there because
of what happened with Marvin.

12:39.291 --> 12:41.875
[sighs]

12:43.542 --> 12:45.375
I'll take the bus.

12:49.542 --> 12:51.000
What the fuck
are you doing?

12:51.000 --> 12:54.291
I need some lunch money.
I got to go too.

12:54.291 --> 12:57.041
[door closes]

12:57.041 --> 12:59.375
[sighs]

13:03.417 --> 13:06.542
Who's the best boy
in the whole world?

13:06.542 --> 13:08.375
You are.

13:19.041 --> 13:22.417
[door buzzes]

13:42.709 --> 13:44.333
But I got
a fucking appointment.

13:44.333 --> 13:46.750
No visitors today.
We're on lockdown.

13:46.750 --> 13:48.792
I don't fucking care.
My son's in there.

13:48.792 --> 13:50.583
I got to see Matty Flynn.
15 minutes.

13:50.583 --> 13:52.709
You don't leave
of your own free will,

13:52.709 --> 13:54.583
you're leaving
in a cop car.

13:54.583 --> 13:57.750
Listen, I'm sorry.
Look, come out here.

13:57.750 --> 13:59.458
Just you and me,
two guys talking.

13:59.458 --> 14:00.959
Come on.

14:13.000 --> 14:14.959
What are you doing here?

14:14.959 --> 14:16.625
Matty Flynn called.
Said he could help.

14:16.625 --> 14:19.542
- Matty Flynn?
- Yeah.

14:19.542 --> 14:21.500
He's a fucking jailhouse lawyer.
He's one of them.

14:21.500 --> 14:22.542
They listen to him.

14:24.875 --> 14:26.291
What are you doing?

14:26.291 --> 14:27.500
You're gonna
bribe him with drugs?

14:27.500 --> 14:28.792
Quiet down.

14:28.792 --> 14:30.291
Are you out
of your fucking mind?

14:30.291 --> 14:32.542
This ain't some
Hollywood bullshit, Ray Ray.

14:32.542 --> 14:33.792
I know these guys.
They kill people.

14:33.792 --> 14:35.208
They're gonna kill Terry.

14:35.208 --> 14:36.500
You think I don't
know that, Mick?

14:36.500 --> 14:38.166
Oh, you know everything.
Yeah, sure.

14:38.166 --> 14:39.792
You're very good at putting
people into these places,

14:39.792 --> 14:41.333
but I'm the one that had
to survive inside.

14:41.333 --> 14:42.583
I know what's going on.

14:42.583 --> 14:45.166
You stay out of this.

14:45.166 --> 14:46.166
Are we understood?

14:47.834 --> 14:49.166
I'm at my end
with you, Mick.

14:49.166 --> 14:50.458
You're gonna need me
on this, Ray.

14:50.458 --> 14:52.875
[scoffs]

14:52.875 --> 14:55.417
I'm gonna need you.

14:55.417 --> 14:58.083
Jesus fucking Christ.

14:59.250 --> 15:00.333
Ray Donovan.

15:00.333 --> 15:03.625
[door buzzes]

15:03.625 --> 15:06.000
[door closes]

15:06.000 --> 15:07.333
[sighs]

15:09.875 --> 15:13.000
[cell phone beeping]

15:15.667 --> 15:18.208
[line trilling]

15:18.208 --> 15:21.083
You can't just leave a kid
in the back of a car, you know.

15:21.083 --> 15:23.041
What are you talking about?

15:23.041 --> 15:24.500
[Abby on phone]
Hello?

15:24.500 --> 15:25.875
I need you to meet me
at the Fite Club.

15:25.875 --> 15:28.041
- What?
- It's important.

15:28.041 --> 15:30.417
I'll explain
everything there. See you.

15:30.417 --> 15:32.417
[indistinct speech on TV]

15:32.417 --> 15:33.834
[sighs]

15:33.834 --> 15:35.834
[Ray]
Can you get him transferred?

15:35.834 --> 15:38.000
It wouldn't change anything.

15:38.000 --> 15:40.083
Anywhere he goes,
his jacket goes with him.

15:40.083 --> 15:42.000
Now, if your brother
had killed a Norteño

15:42.000 --> 15:43.917
or a Blood, man,
maybe I could help you,

15:43.917 --> 15:46.625
but the Aryan Brotherhood,
they've got most of the guards

15:46.625 --> 15:49.875
and the warden
in their fucking pocket.

15:49.875 --> 15:51.291
Why are you
telling me this?

15:51.291 --> 15:53.083
So you'll understand
the fucking magnitude

15:53.083 --> 15:56.208
of the favor
I'm doing for you.

15:58.083 --> 16:00.625
Make it fast.
He's not supposed to be in here.

16:00.625 --> 16:03.542
If I get caught with you here,
I'm fucked.

16:03.542 --> 16:04.875
- S07.
- [door buzzes]

16:04.875 --> 16:08.083
[man over walkie-talkie]
Seven's open.

16:18.834 --> 16:21.083
[sighs]

16:23.083 --> 16:25.917
What the fuck
happened to your face?

16:27.083 --> 16:28.917
What the fuck happened
to yours?

16:30.542 --> 16:33.417
[both chuckling]

16:42.000 --> 16:45.125
[breathing deeply]

16:50.000 --> 16:52.208
You all right, Ter?

16:52.208 --> 16:55.291
- I didn't mean to kill him.
- I know you didn't.

16:55.291 --> 16:56.792
I'm gonna get you
out of here.

16:56.792 --> 16:58.750
Yeah, it doesn't matter
anymore.

16:58.750 --> 17:00.333
Just, uh...

17:00.333 --> 17:02.667
I just need a few hours
to figure it out.

17:02.667 --> 17:04.250
My leg started shaking
a few months back.

17:04.250 --> 17:07.291
You know what that means?

17:07.291 --> 17:09.917
That means I'm three years
from a wheelchair.

17:09.917 --> 17:12.041
Oh, come on.
Don't start talking that--

17:12.041 --> 17:14.959
I don't sleep no more.
I got these fucking visions.

17:16.792 --> 17:19.250
They get me,
they're doing me a favor.

17:19.250 --> 17:21.166
Don't you fucking
quit on me, Terry.

17:22.458 --> 17:24.500
I'm through.

17:24.500 --> 17:27.250
I'm just gonna get worse.

17:27.250 --> 17:29.166
I got nothing
to come back for.

17:29.166 --> 17:32.500
What are you talking about,
you got nothing to go back for?

17:32.500 --> 17:34.417
Who's gonna look after me
if you go down?

17:34.417 --> 17:36.709
Frances don't write me.

17:39.583 --> 17:41.333
The club ain't mine.

17:44.083 --> 17:47.750
My body's shutting down.

17:47.750 --> 17:50.667
[door buzzes, opens]

17:51.667 --> 17:53.166
Time's up.

18:02.333 --> 18:05.709
Kevin's gonna keep you
here in isolation.

18:05.709 --> 18:07.417
I love you, Raymond.

18:12.500 --> 18:15.959
But I don't want
your fucking help.

18:20.875 --> 18:23.542
[sighs]

18:23.542 --> 18:26.417
[groans softly]

18:27.875 --> 18:30.333
[door closes]

18:30.333 --> 18:32.041
- Wettick.
- Is that with a C or a K?

18:32.041 --> 18:34.083
I don't know.
With a fucking K?

18:34.083 --> 18:35.250
[clears throat]

18:35.250 --> 18:36.375
And do you have
a street, sir?

18:36.375 --> 18:38.333
I don't know what street.

18:38.333 --> 18:40.000
- Well, I'm sorry, sir--
- I just need a number.

18:40.000 --> 18:41.125
I'm very sorry, but without
a street name or without--

18:41.125 --> 18:42.709
Oh, fuck.

18:42.709 --> 18:45.417
W-E-T-T-I-C-K?

18:51.041 --> 18:52.959
Judge?

18:54.291 --> 18:57.417
That's fucking him.
Where's the address?

18:57.417 --> 19:00.709
When someone's famous,
their house is hard to find.

19:00.709 --> 19:02.875
[sighs]
What's going on, Mick?

19:02.875 --> 19:04.750
Abby.
Thank God.

19:04.750 --> 19:06.166
Stay here a second.

19:07.500 --> 19:09.083
Who's the kid?

19:09.083 --> 19:11.458
Terry ran into a problem
at the prison.

19:11.458 --> 19:12.875
What kind of problem?

19:12.875 --> 19:15.375
- I can't say.
- Is it that bad?

19:15.375 --> 19:18.709
Yeah, but I got a way to fix it.
I just need some time.

19:18.709 --> 19:20.125
Does Ray know?

19:20.125 --> 19:21.250
I need you
to look after the kid.

19:21.250 --> 19:22.625
I promised her mother--

19:22.625 --> 19:23.917
Oh, for fuck's sakes, Mick.

19:23.917 --> 19:25.166
Look, what else are you
gonna do?

19:25.166 --> 19:27.417
I'll be back
in a couple of hours.

19:27.417 --> 19:29.959
I wouldn't ask you if it wasn't
a fucking life-or-death thing.

19:29.959 --> 19:32.000
You know that.

19:32.000 --> 19:34.000
[sighs]

19:47.500 --> 19:50.333
Judge Wettick.
Uh, my name is Ray Donovan.

19:50.333 --> 19:51.750
I don't know
if you remember me,

19:51.750 --> 19:53.125
but you sentenced
my brother Terry.

19:53.125 --> 19:56.125
Armed robbery,
assault and battery.

19:56.125 --> 19:58.125
I was hoping
we could talk inside.

20:03.792 --> 20:07.291
The Aryans are going after him
because of his Parkinson's.

20:07.291 --> 20:09.458
That's why
all this happened.

20:09.458 --> 20:11.333
Terrible situation.

20:11.333 --> 20:14.208
Yeah. I was, uh,

20:14.208 --> 20:16.792
sort of hoping you might
consider granting him

20:16.792 --> 20:18.959
a compassionate release.

20:18.959 --> 20:22.250
Right.
Because of his Parkinson's.

20:22.250 --> 20:25.041
Prison's no place
for a man like my brother.

20:25.041 --> 20:28.250
Our prison system
has been corrupted.

20:30.125 --> 20:32.625
Private corporations
have turned it

20:32.625 --> 20:35.500
into the new
California Gold Rush.

20:35.500 --> 20:39.417
We've built too many prisons
too fast

20:39.417 --> 20:43.500
and given control away
to the very men we incarcerate.

20:43.500 --> 20:45.667
[sighs]

20:45.667 --> 20:48.083
Terry's a good man.

20:48.083 --> 20:50.125
He doesn't belong
in there.

20:50.125 --> 20:53.291
A good man who was left behind
at an armed robbery.

20:54.709 --> 20:56.125
Yeah.

20:56.125 --> 20:59.542
A good man who murdered
a fellow inmate.

21:01.083 --> 21:02.458
That was self-defense.

21:02.458 --> 21:04.542
That's for the court
to decide.

21:04.542 --> 21:06.959
He'll never make it
to court.

21:06.959 --> 21:09.542
The Aryans
will kill him first.

21:11.625 --> 21:14.375
I can't help you,
Mr. Donovan.

21:16.041 --> 21:17.875
[sighs]

21:30.709 --> 21:33.917
$50,000.

21:33.917 --> 21:37.542
You get the second payment
when my brother's home.

21:37.542 --> 21:40.417
I would have thought you'd have
more imagination than this.

21:47.792 --> 21:50.083
[sighs]

21:50.083 --> 21:53.458
Take the fucking money.

21:56.083 --> 21:58.834
[drawer opens]

21:58.834 --> 21:59.834
[gun cocks]

21:59.834 --> 22:01.959
Leave...now.

22:05.041 --> 22:07.792
Take your money with you.

22:47.041 --> 22:48.875
Ray, what the fuck's
going on?

22:48.875 --> 22:51.125
Mickey dropped that little girl
off with me.

22:51.125 --> 22:53.083
- Said Terry's in trouble.
- [safe beeping]

22:53.083 --> 22:54.792
He killed a guy
in prison.

22:54.792 --> 22:56.333
What?

22:56.333 --> 22:59.792
Oh, my fucking God.

22:59.792 --> 23:01.166
What can I do?

23:04.959 --> 23:06.208
Ray, where's Lena?

23:06.208 --> 23:07.625
She took another job.

23:07.625 --> 23:10.166
You let Lena go?

23:10.166 --> 23:11.667
I'm worried about you, Ray.

23:11.667 --> 23:13.291
I want to help you.

23:13.291 --> 23:14.291
What are you gonna do,
Abs, huh?

23:14.291 --> 23:15.917
Get Terry out of prison?

23:15.917 --> 23:17.834
Talk the fucking Aryan Nation
out of killing him?

23:17.834 --> 23:19.500
What are you gonna do?

23:19.500 --> 23:22.500
I have been
fucking delusional.

23:22.500 --> 23:24.166
Sitting at home,
waiting for you to come back?

23:24.166 --> 23:25.917
That's what this is about.

23:27.166 --> 23:28.458
No.

23:28.458 --> 23:30.500
It's about Terry.

23:30.500 --> 23:32.709
I don't have time for this.

23:32.709 --> 23:35.792
solemn piano music playing

23:35.792 --> 23:40.709
♪♪♪

23:43.709 --> 23:48.041
My mom said if you want to make
a man run fast,

23:48.041 --> 23:50.041
act needy.

23:53.375 --> 23:54.542
I have one
at the Downtown Century.

23:54.542 --> 23:56.333
Good. I'm going
to the Executive Suites.

23:56.333 --> 23:58.000
Do you know how to use
BangBoard?

23:58.000 --> 24:00.542
- Uh, yeah.
- I need more pictures.

24:00.542 --> 24:02.291
Okay. Uh, wait.
Uh, Ginger?

24:02.291 --> 24:04.500
I got to take Cindy and Alex
downtown.

24:04.500 --> 24:05.834
Can you stay and watch over
everything for me

24:05.834 --> 24:07.041
while I'm gone?

24:07.041 --> 24:09.417
No. I have a client.

24:11.000 --> 24:13.208
Shit.

24:13.208 --> 24:15.333
I got to get
to Marina del Rey.

24:15.333 --> 24:17.000
You too. All right.
Uh, fuck it.

24:17.000 --> 24:20.291
Just pile in, everybody.

24:20.291 --> 24:22.417
Hey, where's Mickey?

24:22.417 --> 24:24.166
He left, Bunch.

24:24.166 --> 24:25.667
- Where'd he go?
- Man, I don't know.

24:25.667 --> 24:29.125
Hey, hey, hey, do you have
a camera on your phone?

24:29.125 --> 24:32.166
Yeah. But I got to talk to Papa.
I need to borrow some money.

24:32.166 --> 24:34.542
No, no, no, that's what's up,
'cause this is for Pop.

24:34.542 --> 24:37.709
All right, right here,
this is Michelle, okay?

24:37.709 --> 24:40.041
She needs some pictures taken
for her profile on the website.

24:40.041 --> 24:42.709
Now, you do that, Pop's gonna
hook you up lovely, all right?

24:42.709 --> 24:45.333
He's my brother.

24:45.333 --> 24:47.750
[door closes]

24:49.250 --> 24:51.125
Come on.

24:51.125 --> 24:53.083
Uh...

24:57.250 --> 24:59.375
You can't get my face in.

24:59.375 --> 25:03.125
[cell phone beeping,
camera shutter clicking]

25:03.125 --> 25:05.291
[clears throat]

25:05.291 --> 25:07.542
[cell phone beeping,
camera shutter clicking]

25:07.542 --> 25:11.166
We're very happy that Tara's dad
has come to talk to us

25:11.166 --> 25:13.792
about his exciting work
in law enforcement.

25:13.792 --> 25:16.959
Agent Barnes was instrumental
in hunting down

25:16.959 --> 25:20.125
the notorious criminal
Patrick "Sully" Sullivan.

25:20.125 --> 25:22.250
He capped
that motherfucker!

25:22.250 --> 25:24.250
[laughter]

25:24.250 --> 25:26.792
And Agent Barnes
has recently been named

25:26.792 --> 25:29.041
the Assistant Special Agent
in Charge

25:29.041 --> 25:32.709
of the Los Angeles Bureau
of the FBI.

25:32.709 --> 25:34.500
Agent Barnes.

25:34.500 --> 25:39.208
[applause]

25:39.208 --> 25:42.208
[clears throat]
Wow. Thank you, Lorraine.

25:42.208 --> 25:47.000
It's a real pleasure to be able
to talk to your students.

25:47.000 --> 25:50.208
When I was eight years old,

25:50.208 --> 25:51.667
I stole a Snickers bar

25:51.667 --> 25:55.083
from the local pharmacy
down the street.

25:55.083 --> 25:57.834
Let me tell you, kids,
it's, uh...

26:01.709 --> 26:04.500
It's haunted me ever since.

26:06.750 --> 26:10.000
[indistinct chatter]

26:10.000 --> 26:12.166
Learn anything?

26:12.166 --> 26:14.208
We need to talk, Frank.

26:14.208 --> 26:15.792
You're welcome to come
to my office.

26:15.792 --> 26:18.417
Call my secretary,
and we'll set a time.

26:18.417 --> 26:21.041
I need you to get my brother
out of jail.

26:21.041 --> 26:22.458
What?

26:22.458 --> 26:24.875
I need you to turn
a judge, today.

26:24.875 --> 26:26.041
Go fuck yourself, Ray.

26:30.458 --> 26:33.667
[Kate on recorder]
Who killed Sully Sullivan?

26:33.667 --> 26:35.000
[Frank on recorder]
Mickey Donovan.

26:35.000 --> 26:36.542
Now get off my fucking boat.

26:36.542 --> 26:37.709
- All right.
- [recording continues]

26:37.709 --> 26:39.542
We've been over this
a thousand times.

26:39.542 --> 26:41.542
It's all in the past.
We're even.

26:41.542 --> 26:45.542
Fine.
You just lost your fucking job.

26:45.542 --> 26:48.041
You gonna take us
all down, Ray?

26:48.041 --> 26:49.375
After all this shit,
you're going to open

26:49.375 --> 26:51.208
that fucking box back up?

26:51.208 --> 26:52.417
He's my brother, Frank.

26:52.417 --> 26:54.542
Come on, Ray.
Don't do this.

26:54.542 --> 26:56.709
All right,
what judge sentenced him?

26:57.917 --> 26:59.750
Wettick.

26:59.750 --> 27:01.166
[sighs]

27:01.166 --> 27:03.250
All right, what do you
want me to do?

27:03.250 --> 27:05.834
He's up for re-election.

27:05.834 --> 27:07.917
I want you to go after him
for campaign fraud.

27:07.917 --> 27:10.417
- What if he's clean?
- Doesn't matter.

27:10.417 --> 27:12.917
Once the press gets wind of it,
kills his campaign either way.

27:15.583 --> 27:18.667
If I do it, you give me
that fucking tape.

27:20.792 --> 27:23.500
You do this,
you'll never see me again.

27:27.834 --> 27:29.166
[funk music plays on computer]

27:29.166 --> 27:30.417
[computer beeps]

27:30.417 --> 27:32.417
♪♪♪

27:32.417 --> 27:34.417
Fuck.

27:34.417 --> 27:35.959
[knock at door]

27:38.250 --> 27:40.542
Where's Daryll?

27:40.542 --> 27:43.583
Um, I'm his brother,
Bunchy.

27:43.583 --> 27:46.083
Huh.
I need breast milk.

27:46.083 --> 27:47.625
What?

27:47.625 --> 27:49.208
Breast milk.
It's for one of my johns.

27:49.208 --> 27:51.625
It's really important.

27:51.625 --> 27:53.792
Where am I gonna get
breast milk?

27:53.792 --> 27:56.166
I don't know.
Gary always had it.

27:56.166 --> 27:57.959
Who's Gary?

27:57.959 --> 28:00.709
Look, I need it within an hour,
and I'm not fucking around.

28:00.709 --> 28:02.917
This guy pays a lot.

28:02.917 --> 28:06.959
♪♪♪

28:06.959 --> 28:09.542
No possession
of a police radio...

28:09.542 --> 28:13.083
- [camera shutter clicking]
- ...or a scanner.

28:13.083 --> 28:15.875
No firearms, no knives,

28:15.875 --> 28:19.125
and no leaving town.

28:19.125 --> 28:20.583
Okay, now,

28:20.583 --> 28:24.375
I have a very important
question for you.

28:24.375 --> 28:25.792
Yeah?

28:28.417 --> 28:29.959
How many dates
with a new lady friend

28:29.959 --> 28:32.917
before you try
to seal the deal?

28:32.917 --> 28:34.875
Now, you know, I'm talking
about a woman in her 40s

28:34.875 --> 28:36.583
with some refinement,
nice ass.

28:36.583 --> 28:38.000
[door opens]

28:38.000 --> 28:40.166
Get out.
Get the fuck out.

28:40.166 --> 28:41.750
Get out.

28:43.500 --> 28:45.333
Terry killed an Aryan
in County.

28:45.333 --> 28:47.250
Oh, boy, boy, boy, boy.

28:47.250 --> 28:48.625
You got to help me
get him out.

28:48.625 --> 28:51.333
I'm a fucking
parole officer, Mick.

28:51.333 --> 28:53.834
I deal with ex-cons.
I don't have that kind of clout.

28:53.834 --> 28:55.417
I need you to get me
to his judge.

28:55.417 --> 28:57.333
- Me?
- Wettick. You know him?

28:57.333 --> 29:00.166
I know all of them, but I just
can't fucking go after--

29:00.166 --> 29:03.125
You piece of shit.
My son's life is at stake.

29:03.125 --> 29:05.250
You're as responsible as I am
for putting him in there,

29:05.250 --> 29:06.500
and I'll make sure
everyone knows it

29:06.500 --> 29:08.041
if you don't get me
to that judge.

29:08.041 --> 29:09.625
Jesus Christ, Mick.

29:09.625 --> 29:11.291
This is my boy
I'm talking about.

29:11.291 --> 29:14.542
You're going to get me
to that judge.

29:14.542 --> 29:16.750
I'll give myself up.
I won't turn you in.

29:16.750 --> 29:19.875
But you're gonna tell me
where that sucker lives.

29:23.709 --> 29:24.875
I'm at the grocery store.

29:24.875 --> 29:26.625
[Ginger on phone]
What?

29:26.625 --> 29:30.542
Well, I'm trying to figure out,
you know, which one to...

29:30.542 --> 29:32.291
Hold on.

29:32.291 --> 29:34.375
Hello. Excuse me.

29:34.375 --> 29:37.166
Which one tastes like
the real thing?

29:37.166 --> 29:39.375
No sé.

29:39.375 --> 29:41.917
[sighs]

29:41.917 --> 29:46.667
I'm just gonna get the most
expensive formula they have.

29:46.667 --> 29:48.667
No, no, no, no, that's--
that's not going to work.

29:48.667 --> 29:51.041
I tried that once,
and he fucking flipped out.

29:51.041 --> 29:53.500
- Well, what do I do?
- I don't know.

29:53.500 --> 29:55.625
Figure it out.

29:55.625 --> 29:57.500
Oh, and I need
adult diapers.

29:59.333 --> 30:02.125
[sighs]

30:02.125 --> 30:04.041
[baby babbling]

30:04.041 --> 30:06.917
speaking Spanish

30:09.583 --> 30:12.125
[can clatters]

30:12.125 --> 30:14.250
You sure this is
where Mickey lives?

30:14.250 --> 30:16.083
Yeah.

30:16.083 --> 30:19.917
I'm not supposed to be here
while my mom's working.

30:19.917 --> 30:21.750
[sighs]
It's frozen.

30:21.750 --> 30:22.750
[pop music playing on computer]

30:22.750 --> 30:24.667
[computer beeps]

30:24.667 --> 30:29.750
♪♪♪

30:34.875 --> 30:37.291
What the fuck
is going on here?

30:39.000 --> 30:40.417
Hi, Mommy.

30:40.417 --> 30:42.458
Hi, baby,
what are you doing here?

30:42.458 --> 30:45.083
You need to go home.

30:45.083 --> 30:46.417
Oh.

30:46.417 --> 30:47.667
Thank you.

30:47.667 --> 30:48.917
[scoffs]

30:48.917 --> 30:52.458
You should be
fucking ashamed of yourself.

30:52.458 --> 30:55.000
It's just part-time.

30:56.375 --> 30:58.709
[baby cries]

31:01.041 --> 31:02.792
I can't fix
his nose in here.

31:02.792 --> 31:05.500
Just finish
stitching him up.

31:11.000 --> 31:12.959
- Open 07.
- Opening 07.

31:12.959 --> 31:14.792
- [door buzzes]
- You didn't have to bring him.

31:14.792 --> 31:16.542
Tell that
to your brother.

31:16.542 --> 31:18.291
You're a good fighter, man.

31:18.291 --> 31:19.959
Where did you get
that fucking uppercut of yours?

31:19.959 --> 31:21.000
What the--

31:26.667 --> 31:28.458
You're dead, motherfucker.

31:28.458 --> 31:30.333
You're a dead ding,
you son of a bitch!

31:30.333 --> 31:33.375
[yelling]

31:34.709 --> 31:37.000
You're dead!

31:37.000 --> 31:39.959
You son of a bitch!
I'm going to kill you!

31:39.959 --> 31:41.792
I'm going to cut
your fucking head off!

31:41.792 --> 31:43.458
[Frank]
Should have taken my car

31:43.458 --> 31:44.458
and used the light.

31:44.458 --> 31:46.792
[cell phone ringing]

31:46.792 --> 31:48.208
Yeah.

31:48.208 --> 31:50.500
They shivved the prison doctor,
motherfucker.

31:50.500 --> 31:51.875
- What?
- We're done.

31:51.875 --> 31:54.083
Warden took me
off of my detail.

31:54.083 --> 31:57.166
Terry's going back
to Gen-Pop.

31:57.166 --> 31:59.500
- [tires squealing]
- What the fuck are you doing?

31:59.500 --> 32:01.125
- Call the judge.
- What?

32:01.125 --> 32:02.750
Call the fucking judge.

32:03.917 --> 32:07.125
[horns blaring]

32:09.583 --> 32:11.458
[Mickey]
Nice flowers.

32:13.667 --> 32:15.291
What can I do for you?

32:15.291 --> 32:16.834
My name is
Mickey Donovan.

32:16.834 --> 32:19.083
I was hoping we could
have a conversation.

32:21.709 --> 32:25.000
I'm going to tell you
what I told your son.

32:25.000 --> 32:26.458
I can't be bought.

32:26.458 --> 32:28.208
My boy went to prison
for my actions.

32:28.208 --> 32:29.875
I was the one
who organized the robbery.

32:29.875 --> 32:31.125
It was me.

32:31.125 --> 32:32.458
If you wanted
to help your son,

32:32.458 --> 32:33.792
you should have done it
four months ago.

32:33.792 --> 32:36.917
So you're saying,
let him die.

32:36.917 --> 32:39.041
I'm saying
that's not the way it works.

32:39.041 --> 32:41.083
I'll tell you
the way it works.

32:41.083 --> 32:42.500
You're gonna get
on that phone.

32:42.500 --> 32:44.125
You're gonna call
whoever you got to call,

32:44.125 --> 32:45.917
get my son out.

32:48.750 --> 32:50.083
Get off
my property.

32:50.083 --> 32:51.583
You got to be
fucking kidding me.

32:51.583 --> 32:52.834
[grunts]

32:52.834 --> 32:54.333
- Call who you need to call.
- No.

32:54.333 --> 32:56.750
Sitting up there,
in your fucking robes.

32:56.750 --> 32:57.750
You think you're God.

32:57.750 --> 32:59.291
You're not up there
anymore.

32:59.291 --> 33:00.917
You're down here
with the lower people,

33:00.917 --> 33:02.417
and down here, I decide
who lives and dies.

33:02.417 --> 33:03.959
- No, no, no, no, no.
- Make the fucking call.

33:03.959 --> 33:06.458
- Make the call.
- No! I need my pills.

33:06.458 --> 33:08.083
Fuck you.

33:08.083 --> 33:09.583
[groans]

33:09.583 --> 33:12.083
[thud]

33:22.458 --> 33:23.792
[door opens]

33:28.750 --> 33:30.000
What did you do?

33:30.000 --> 33:32.333
He just fell down.

33:32.333 --> 33:35.208
Oh, shit.

33:39.417 --> 33:40.959
Come on.

33:43.625 --> 33:45.125
Come on.

33:45.125 --> 33:46.959
- [cell phone beeping]
- What are you doing?

33:46.959 --> 33:48.000
Calling an ambulance.

33:48.000 --> 33:50.000
Put the fucking phone down.

33:55.500 --> 33:57.291
Don't die.

33:57.291 --> 34:00.041
Come on,
please don't fucking die.

34:05.500 --> 34:06.625
Come on.

34:06.625 --> 34:08.542
Breathe.
Breathe!

34:13.834 --> 34:15.166
Oh, fuck.

34:16.083 --> 34:18.625
Oh, fuck.

34:18.625 --> 34:21.166
[sighs]

34:26.834 --> 34:29.834
Everything you touch
turns to shit.

34:29.834 --> 34:31.250
Don't say that.

34:34.709 --> 34:36.166
Ray?

34:42.000 --> 34:44.333
You just killed
another one of your kids, Mick.

34:47.125 --> 34:48.625
Clean it up.

34:49.542 --> 34:51.208
We even?

34:52.375 --> 34:54.208
Ray, are we even?

35:00.000 --> 35:02.458
I'll--I'll tell them
it was me, Ray.

35:02.458 --> 35:06.375
I'll tell them it was me.
I'll trade my life for Terry's.

35:06.375 --> 35:09.458
Come on, Ray.
We can still fix this.

35:09.458 --> 35:10.583
Ray?

35:12.208 --> 35:14.875
- Come on, Ray.
- [car door opens, closes]

35:14.875 --> 35:17.542
[engine starts]

35:17.542 --> 35:20.417
[tires squealing]

35:22.375 --> 35:24.417
God.

35:24.417 --> 35:26.208
[Abby]
I'm home.

35:26.208 --> 35:29.166
[video game beeping]
[dog panting]

35:33.709 --> 35:35.625
Would somebody
fucking say hello?

35:35.625 --> 35:37.250
Hey, Mom.

35:41.750 --> 35:43.792
Hey, big guy.

35:43.792 --> 35:46.125
Hi.
You need to go out?

35:46.125 --> 35:49.750
Conor? Can you take him out
while I make his dinner?

35:49.750 --> 35:51.792
Put on his leash.

36:00.208 --> 36:03.083
- [barking]
- Conor! Grab him!

36:03.083 --> 36:05.542
[barking continues]

36:05.542 --> 36:06.417
Dog!

36:07.750 --> 36:09.125
Dog!

36:13.041 --> 36:14.834
[sighs]

36:30.083 --> 36:33.125
pensive music playing

36:33.125 --> 36:38.208
♪♪♪

36:56.000 --> 36:59.333
[engine starts]

36:59.333 --> 37:02.208
[tires squealing]

37:08.417 --> 37:11.458
dramatic music playing

37:11.458 --> 37:16.333
♪♪♪

37:22.166 --> 37:24.959
[Huey Lewis]
No, don't. Don't. Don't.

37:24.959 --> 37:27.000
- Open 27.
- No. No.

37:27.000 --> 37:29.000
- [door buzzes]
- Please, no.

37:31.834 --> 37:32.875
Close 27.

37:32.875 --> 37:36.542
No. Please.
Wait. Help.

37:36.542 --> 37:41.083
Please.
Let--let me out.

37:41.083 --> 37:44.208
Let me out.

37:44.208 --> 37:46.375
They can be cruel.

37:46.375 --> 37:49.583
Don't leave me with him.
Please. Please.

37:56.208 --> 37:57.792
Mr. Finney
will see you now.

38:09.208 --> 38:11.375
Thank you, Varick.

38:19.542 --> 38:21.250
You want some coffee?

38:25.917 --> 38:28.417
Have a seat, please.

38:29.709 --> 38:30.834
Mr. Finney--

38:30.834 --> 38:33.792
Ray, Ray.

38:33.792 --> 38:35.917
Take a breath, huh?

38:55.667 --> 38:58.291
You want to tell me
about it?

39:02.083 --> 39:04.625
My, uh...

39:06.959 --> 39:10.250
My brother's in prison.

39:10.250 --> 39:12.792
He killed another inmate,
self-defense.

39:20.375 --> 39:22.458
The other guys, uh...

39:24.917 --> 39:26.709
...they're gonna kill him.

39:26.709 --> 39:29.583
That's terrible.

39:29.583 --> 39:33.000
I need to
get him out

39:33.000 --> 39:34.458
tonight.

39:39.417 --> 39:41.709
Can you help me?

39:43.250 --> 39:46.500
[man speaking indistinctly
on TV]

39:52.166 --> 39:56.041
[sighs]

39:56.041 --> 39:58.959
So how'd it go,
Bunch?

39:58.959 --> 40:00.834
Fine.

40:00.834 --> 40:03.417
How about you?

40:03.417 --> 40:04.792
Easy breezy, man.

40:04.792 --> 40:07.500
[chuckles]
I was born to pimp.

40:12.750 --> 40:13.709
Hey, Pop.

40:15.917 --> 40:18.542
How's Terry doing?

40:18.542 --> 40:21.750
- What happened to Terry?
- Nothing.

40:21.750 --> 40:24.208
Wait a minute.
I thought that's why you left.

40:24.208 --> 40:25.750
What are you doing here,
Bunchy?

40:25.750 --> 40:29.375
Oh, I needed some help
with the girls.

40:29.375 --> 40:32.959
Ain't that wonderful?
Working with your brother.

40:34.208 --> 40:35.834
[dog food rattles]

40:35.834 --> 40:37.041
Dog?

40:39.750 --> 40:41.834
[dog food rattles]

40:41.834 --> 40:44.291
Dog?

40:48.709 --> 40:51.041
Dog?

41:04.208 --> 41:07.333
[flashlight clatters]

41:09.083 --> 41:12.166
[sobbing]

41:28.291 --> 41:30.083
Stop it.

41:30.083 --> 41:32.125
Fucking stop it.

41:46.625 --> 41:49.625
How many children
in your family?

41:50.625 --> 41:54.125
Um, I have
three brothers.

41:54.125 --> 41:56.125
I had a sister.

41:56.125 --> 41:57.583
She died?

41:57.583 --> 41:59.291
Yeah.

42:01.333 --> 42:03.125
She died.

42:05.125 --> 42:06.792
I'm an only child.

42:06.792 --> 42:09.166
Missed out on all that
social Darwinism.

42:09.166 --> 42:12.542
Didn't have to compete
for my parents' attention.

42:13.875 --> 42:15.959
You must be
in the middle.

42:18.750 --> 42:23.458
Yeah, I bet your brothers are
helpless compared with you, huh?

42:26.125 --> 42:27.875
I don't know.

42:40.375 --> 42:43.291
Governor Verona
will not be happy.

42:43.291 --> 42:45.083
Cusp of an election.

42:45.083 --> 42:47.667
Numbers are tight.

42:50.333 --> 42:52.458
[indistinct chatter]

42:52.458 --> 42:55.875
Mr. Finney.
Please, this way.

43:00.875 --> 43:02.250
Andrew.

43:02.250 --> 43:03.709
Tom.

43:03.709 --> 43:06.917
This is my good friend
Ray Donovan.

43:06.917 --> 43:08.500
Nice to meet you.

43:08.500 --> 43:11.250
So how are
the polls looking?

43:11.250 --> 43:12.709
We're getting there.

43:12.709 --> 43:15.375
[chuckling]
You have my every confidence.

43:18.208 --> 43:19.709
Gentlemen.

43:27.000 --> 43:29.500
So, Andrew,

43:29.500 --> 43:33.709
what can I do for you?

43:33.709 --> 43:37.542
My friend Ray has a problem
that only you can address.

43:37.542 --> 43:38.917
I see.

43:38.917 --> 43:42.458
Ray has a brother
in County.

43:42.458 --> 43:45.709
He's also
a Parkinson's sufferer.

43:45.709 --> 43:48.667
Ray was working on getting him
compassionate release

43:48.667 --> 43:51.583
when there was an unfortunate
incident with another inmate.

43:51.583 --> 43:54.291
Andrew, it's not the time--

43:54.291 --> 43:55.583
We would appreciate it

43:55.583 --> 43:57.500
if you would expedite
his release.

43:57.500 --> 43:59.417
And if he gets out
and fucks up again?

43:59.417 --> 44:02.667
He won't.
You have our assurances.

44:02.667 --> 44:04.542
If the press hears of this

44:04.542 --> 44:06.583
and my opponent
decides to run with it?

44:06.583 --> 44:08.917
We'll deal
with the press.

44:12.542 --> 44:15.834
I'll pardon him one week
after I win my second term.

44:15.834 --> 44:17.583
That's just
a few weeks away.

44:17.583 --> 44:20.375
You need to
pardon him tonight.

44:20.375 --> 44:24.041
My platform has been
cracking down on crime,

44:24.041 --> 44:26.250
not releasing prisoners.

44:26.250 --> 44:28.917
[sighs]

44:28.917 --> 44:32.834
This is taking far longer
than I thought it would.

44:34.750 --> 44:37.291
[sighs]

44:40.250 --> 44:42.542
I'll get it done
tonight.

44:43.750 --> 44:45.291
Thank you, Tom.

44:45.291 --> 44:47.792
I appreciate
your friendship, Andrew,

44:47.792 --> 44:50.917
and your continued support.

44:50.917 --> 44:52.792
Of course.

44:53.917 --> 44:56.792
[door opens]

45:07.458 --> 45:09.500
Mr. Finney,
I just wanted to say--

45:09.500 --> 45:11.667
Anything for a friend.

45:22.583 --> 45:26.333
It was a pleasure
to see you tonight, Ray.

45:26.333 --> 45:28.709
[door closes]

45:32.542 --> 45:35.834
Sign there,
there, and there.

45:37.291 --> 45:38.667
Your salary is set.

45:38.667 --> 45:40.500
The terms of your deal
are for one year

45:40.500 --> 45:43.500
with an option to extend
to another at our discretion.

45:45.291 --> 45:46.750
Whatever
Mr. Finney wants.

45:48.917 --> 45:51.667
You'll be expected for work
tomorrow morning.

45:51.667 --> 45:53.583
You can see
yourself out.

46:00.375 --> 46:02.375
[door closes]

46:12.208 --> 46:15.458
I thought you were through
with the Finney family, Ray.

46:20.250 --> 46:22.875
[scoffs]

46:36.917 --> 46:38.125
[knock at door]

46:38.125 --> 46:39.917
Come in.

46:48.917 --> 46:52.250
You're in charge.

46:52.250 --> 46:53.834
What?

46:53.834 --> 46:56.834
I need to go away
for a couple of days, Bridge.

46:56.834 --> 46:57.917
Why?

47:01.291 --> 47:04.166
I just need
a couple of days.

47:04.166 --> 47:06.250
Where are you going?

47:06.250 --> 47:08.417
I don't know.

47:08.417 --> 47:11.583
Someplace I can think.

47:11.583 --> 47:13.667
You can't be serious, Mom.

47:13.667 --> 47:15.750
I am.

47:22.417 --> 47:24.625
Look after
your brother.

47:24.625 --> 47:26.709
Love you.

47:34.458 --> 47:35.959
Mom?

47:37.583 --> 47:39.208
